So `KnownBits.getMaxValue()` returns `~Zero`, which is the maximum possible value given the known zero bits.

I can use this to check if X + mask would overflow:
```cpp
KnownBits XKnown = computeKnownBits(X, &I);
APInt MaxX = XKnown.getMaxValue();
APInt MaxSum = MaxX + *MaskC;
if (MaxSum.ult(MaxX) || MaxSum.ult(*MaskC)) {
  // Overflow would occur
  return nullptr;
}
```

Actually, for unsigned addition, overflow occurs if `a + b < a` or `a + b < b`. So I can check:
```cpp
if (MaxX.ugt(APInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth) - *MaskC)) {
  // MaxX + mask would overflow
  return nullptr;
}
```

Or more simply:
```cpp
if ((MaxX + *MaskC).ult(MaxX)) {
  // Overflow
  return nullptr;
}
```

Let me update the implementation to include this check:

